@startuml
title Public Resume Processing — AI-Orchestrated, Event-Driven, Real-Time UX
autonumber

skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FDF6E3
skinparam noteBorderColor #657B83
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam participantPadding 12
skinparam BoxPadding 10

actor "Candidate FE\n(Public Angular)" as FE
participant "Gateway\n(YARP)" as GW
participant "Monolith API\n(System of Record)" as MON
database "Monolith DB\n(SQL Server)" as MSQL
participant "Outbox Processor" as OBX
participant "AI Service v2\n(Orchestrator + SignalR)" as AI
participant "OpenAI API" as OAI
database "Embeddings DB\n(PostgreSQL + pgvector)" as PG

== SYNCHRONOUS PATH — Fast User Acknowledgment ==

FE -> GW: Upload resume
activate GW
GW -> MON: POST /api/resumes
activate MON

MON -> MSQL: INSERT Resume + INSERT Outbox
activate MSQL
note right of MSQL
Atomic transaction boundary:
- Persist resume metadata
- Write outbox event
Single commit ensures consistency
end note
MSQL --> MON: committed
deactivate MSQL

MON --> GW: 202 Accepted
deactivate MON
GW --> FE: Upload accepted
deactivate GW

note over FE
User receives immediate response.
System prioritizes UX latency over full processing.
end note

== ASYNCHRONOUS PATH — Event-Driven Processing ==

OBX -> AI: resume.uploaded (event)
activate AI

note over AI
End-to-end pipeline (~17–18s):
- Parsing
- Progressive updates
- Embeddings
- Matching + explanations
end note

== Phase 1 — Progressive Resume Parsing ==

AI -> OAI: Parse resume (LLM)
activate OAI
note right of OAI
~4.9s
Structured extraction
~2.6k tokens
end note
OAI --> AI: structured resume
deactivate OAI

AI -> MON: Save parsed section
activate MON
MON -> MSQL: UPDATE resume content
activate MSQL
MSQL --> MON: committed
deactivate MSQL
MON --> AI: OK
deactivate MON

AI -> FE: SignalR ResumeSectionParsed ("quick")

note over FE
First section appears immediately.
UX becomes responsive early.
end note

AI -> MON: Save additional section
activate MON
MON -> MSQL: UPDATE resume content
activate MSQL
MSQL --> MON: committed
deactivate MSQL
MON --> AI: OK
deactivate MON

AI -> FE: SignalR ResumeSectionParsed ("workHistory")

note over FE
UI progressively hydrates
as parsing continues.
end note

== Phase 2 — Embeddings Generation ==

AI -> OAI: Generate embeddings
activate OAI
note right of OAI
Batch embeddings (~1.06s)
~11k characters processed
end note
OAI --> AI: vectors
deactivate OAI

AI -> PG: Upsert embeddings
activate PG
PG --> AI: stored
deactivate PG

== Phase 3 — Match Resolution + Explanation Generation ==

note over AI,FE
SignalR-driven orchestration (push model):

AI emits events → UI reacts →
triggers downstream enrichment pipeline.

No polling required.
System is event-driven and reactive.
end note

FE -> GW: Request matches
activate GW
GW -> MON: GET /resumes/{id}/matching
activate MON

MON -> AI: Resolve matches + explanations
activate AI

AI -> PG: Check cached explanations
activate PG
note right of PG: cache miss
PG --> AI: none
deactivate PG

AI -> OAI: Generate explanations
activate OAI
note right of OAI
~24s total
10 explanations
~3.9k tokens
expensive, uncached path
end note
OAI --> AI: explanations
deactivate OAI

AI -> PG: Persist explanations
activate PG
PG --> AI: saved
deactivate PG

AI --> MON: matches + explanations
deactivate AI

MON --> GW: 200 OK
deactivate MON
GW --> FE: results
deactivate GW

== Phase 4 — Final Real-Time UX ==

AI -> FE: SignalR FinalUpdates

note over FE
Final user experience:
- Resume parsed progressively
- Matches computed via embeddings
- AI explanations generated
- UI updated in real time

No blocking. No polling.
end note

deactivate AI

@enduml